					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The NES PPU refreshes (AFAIK) at 60Hz (or 60 frames per second). The pAPU uses these modes:
<br />
<br />- 60Hz = 1 update in a frame (read 'update' as 'clock').
<br />- 120Hz = 2 updates in a frame.
<br />- 240Hz = 4 updates in a frame.
<br />
<br />When 4017h is written &amp; set the frame sequencer, there's 4 ("normal") or 5 steps (+1), up to specific bit $80. Every step (AFAIK) takes 1/4th of frame.
<br />
<br />-- AFAIK = as far as I know of... <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /></div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><strong>Zepper</strong><br /><a href="http://rocknes.web.fc2.com/" class="postlink"><em>RockNES developer</em></a></div>
